00:24:07,546 --> 00:24:09,207
I'll leave.
- Live long.

249
00:24:14,519 --> 00:24:19,422
His blood pressure is high.
- ls he worried about something?

250
00:24:20,258 --> 00:24:23,159
Doctor, you know that
no one except you came..

251
00:24:23,228 --> 00:24:25,458
..in the Saturday gathering
in the last three weeks.

252
00:24:26,264 --> 00:24:28,425
How can I tell him why
other people don't come?

253
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:33,226
Come.

254
00:24:38,510 --> 00:24:39,499
Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

255
00:24:49,488 --> 00:24:51,456
You know, I just can't
get over it, friend.

256
00:24:52,557 --> 00:24:55,458
How did they come to know that
Sameer was a dormant partner?

257
00:24:56,561 --> 00:24:58,256
Because big brother's watching.

258
00:24:58,563 --> 00:25:00,531
What?
- Did you read?

259
00:25:01,299 --> 00:25:03,529
They have got databases of
all Muslim-owned businesses.

260
00:25:04,503 --> 00:25:05,492
Yes, but..

261
00:25:06,571 --> 00:25:09,233
Apart from some bank
papers and legal documents..

262
00:25:09,307 --> 00:25:10,569
..Sameer's name shows nowhere, friend.

263
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:15,245
Ketki, leave it. Now, I
don't want to ask all this.

264
00:25:16,314 --> 00:25:17,474
Yes, leave it.

265
00:25:25,590 --> 00:25:30,254
I had promised Sameer
that I will learn this.

266
00:25:30,595 --> 00:25:32,256
And now see. Now, it's the last day.

267
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:36,528
He is really fond of tea.

268
00:25:37,335 --> 00:25:39,269
ln his family, all are fond of it.

269
00:25:39,571 --> 00:25:42,607
ln fact, father says that
Muslims are allowed more tea..

270
00:25:42,607 --> 00:25:44,268
..because they are not allowed alcohol.

271
00:25:45,277 --> 00:25:46,301
But Sameer drinks.

272
00:25:47,345 --> 00:25:49,506
And I have never seen
him pray or anything.

273
00:25:50,649 --> 00:25:54,585
Really, he is so not a Muslim.
- But he is, Ketki.

274
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:56,587
He is.

275
00:25:57,589 --> 00:25:59,624
Somewhere on the list in
big bold letters is written..

276
00:25:59,624 --> 00:26:01,285
..Sameer Arshad Sheikh.

277
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:04,590
I was not joking when I said
that big brother is watching.

278
00:26:08,733 --> 00:26:10,291
Tell me honestly, Anu.

279
00:26:11,670 --> 00:26:13,934
Do you ever regret marrying a Muslim?

280
00:26:14,005 --> 00:26:15,336
No.

281
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:21,637
When we got married, I knew
it was not going to be easy.

282
00:26:23,615 --> 00:26:26,345
But this last month has taken that
to a completely different level.

283
00:26:27,385 --> 00:26:28,545
What do you think?

284
00:26:28,653 --> 00:26:31,554
Delhi is going to be
much different from here.

285
00:26:33,858 --> 00:26:37,555
Your brother is also
there. ln U.S. of A.

286
00:26:39,864 --> 00:26:41,593
His life is hardly a picnic, friend.

287
00:26:42,634 --> 00:26:45,626
So what you are saying is that
no matter where I go I'm done for.

288
00:26:45,870 --> 00:26:50,330
What I'm saying is, this is
your home. Just leave the rest.

289
00:26:51,710 --> 00:26:53,337
It is easy for you to say.

290
00:26:55,647 --> 00:26:58,639
You don't have to hide if some
Hindu fundamentalist kills someone.

291
00:27:00,418 --> 00:27:03,353
If some lslamic extremist
bombs someplace in the world..

292
00:27:04,723 --> 00:27:06,384
..we've to hang our heads in shame.

293
00:27:08,627 --> 00:27:09,594
What?

294
00:27:10,428 --> 00:27:11,395
We?

295
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:23,373
I don't know 'me' became 'we'.
- Tea is ready.

296
00:27:24,676 --> 00:27:25,665
Coming.

297
00:27:30,682 --> 00:27:31,671
Sister, take some more.

298
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:33,411
You can never say what
happens at such times.

299
00:27:33,752 --> 00:27:35,686
No, it's very expensive.

300
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:42,619
Mother!
- Hey, can't you see? You are running blindly.

301
00:27:47,465 --> 00:27:48,454
Did you hurt yourself?

302
00:27:54,439 --> 00:27:56,669
Are you hungry?

303
00:27:59,678 --> 00:28:01,771
Come, come with me.

304
00:28:07,485 --> 00:28:08,452
Come.

305
00:28:30,008 --> 00:28:37,471
Are you a Muslim? What is your name?
- Mohsin.

306
00:28:49,561 --> 00:28:51,495
Take this. Eat it.

307
00:29:07,078 --> 00:29:11,515
Aarti.
- Coming, Father.

308
00:29:12,851 --> 00:29:14,512
'Did Kesar return?'

309
00:29:18,022 --> 00:29:19,512
Later, okay.

310
00:29:21,292 --> 00:29:22,281
Come.

311
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:33,359
Come.

312
00:29:36,374 --> 00:29:38,274
No, he has sent a child.

313
00:29:38,810 --> 00:29:40,277
Where is he?

314
00:29:42,380 --> 00:29:44,314
Come. Come.

315
00:29:48,353 --> 00:29:51,379
Go to father. There is
no need to be scared.

316
00:29:51,456 --> 00:29:55,324
He can't even stand.
- Come here. - Go.

317
00:29:59,464 --> 00:30:00,431
What is your name?

318
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:02,433
Mohan.

319
00:30:05,470 --> 00:30:08,405
He is so small. What work can he do?

320
00:30:09,474 --> 00:30:10,441
Come here.

321
00:30:17,482 --> 00:30:18,449
Go and wash it.

322
00:31:07,532 --> 00:31:09,397
Amen.
- Amen.

323
00:31:14,439 --> 00:31:15,428
Come. Let's go.

324
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:25,381
Father did so much for our neighbours.

325
00:31:25,483 --> 00:31:28,509
But so few people came at such a moment.

326
00:31:30,421 --> 00:31:31,388
Yes, dear.

327
00:31:32,257 --> 00:31:36,125
More people would have come
if it was an ordinary priest.

328
00:31:38,162 --> 00:31:39,288
Well, I'm pleased
that you came at least.

329
00:31:40,164 --> 00:31:43,156
He doesn't go anywhere. But
he insisted to come here.

330
00:31:43,334 --> 00:31:49,136
It was my duty to
come. Don't worry, dear.

331
00:31:50,241 --> 00:31:52,209
God is the giver.

332
00:31:53,244 --> 00:31:57,237
Father was exactly like
you. Hardly any earnings.

333
00:31:58,249 --> 00:32:01,218
A house which may
topple over at anytime.

334
00:32:02,186 --> 00:32:04,279
And he would say that God is the giver.

335
00:32:07,191 --> 00:32:13,152
If you need anything, ask
me unhesitatingly. Okay?

336
00:32:14,332 --> 00:32:17,199
I should leave now.
- Have some lentil pilaf at least.

337
00:32:17,268 --> 00:32:20,328
No, I will eat something after
I'm done with my medicines.

338
00:32:22,206 --> 00:32:23,195
Live long.

339
00:32:33,217 --> 00:32:34,352
The idiot saw us and left.

340
00:32:34,352 --> 00:32:39,187
Who will take two oldies?
- You have decided not to see.

341
00:32:42,327 --> 00:32:44,227
Will you go to Hirabaug society?
- No.

342
00:32:47,332 --> 00:32:49,323
What happened?
- What will happen? Shook his head.

343
00:32:50,268 --> 00:32:53,362
Maybe he doesn't want
to go to that side.

344
00:32:54,238 --> 00:32:56,331
Why will a Muslim go to that area?

345
00:32:57,241 --> 00:33:01,200
lsn't his life dear to him?
- You are too much.

346
00:33:01,379 --> 00:33:05,247
Do one thing, wait here. I'll
go and look at the corner.

347
00:33:32,076 --> 00:33:36,035
How much is this sugar candy for?
- Rs.20 per kilo.

348
00:33:38,082 --> 00:33:41,074
Rs.20 a kilo.
- Leave it, Brother.

349
00:33:41,152 --> 00:33:43,211
It's enough if you get
sugar candy at such times.

350
00:33:45,223 --> 00:33:46,212
Mr. Khan.

351
00:33:47,091 --> 00:33:51,050
Mr. Khan, come. Come. I
told you to wait there. You.

352
00:33:51,129 --> 00:33:55,122
Come. Sit. Let's go.

353
00:34:02,106 --> 00:34:06,167
Rs.20 a kilo. -
What? - Sugar candy.

354
00:34:08,179 --> 00:34:10,147
Have you found the prices these days?

355
00:34:11,115 --> 00:34:13,140
And you wanted to help Sakina.

356
00:34:14,118 --> 00:34:16,109
What would you give
her if she really asked?

357
00:34:17,088 --> 00:34:19,147
Your old sitar or the broken TV.

358
00:34:21,259 --> 00:34:22,248
Stop him. Stop him.

359
00:34:23,127 --> 00:34:25,152
Hey. - Stop him.
- Hey. Stop him.

360
00:34:27,265 --> 00:34:31,224
Why are you stopping him?
Look. Where are you going?

361
00:34:31,302 --> 00:34:34,135
Mr. Khan. Listen. Hey.

362
00:34:34,205 --> 00:34:37,275
Where is the mosque?
- Where are you going?

363
00:34:37,275 --> 00:34:39,243
The Wali mosque was here.

364
00:34:40,178 --> 00:34:43,204
Hey. You would have been
hurt. What are you doing?

365
00:34:45,149 --> 00:34:48,209
The Wali mosque was here.
- They broke it in the riots.

366
00:34:49,220 --> 00:34:52,087
Shut up. You have lost your mind.

367
00:34:52,156 --> 00:34:57,287
No, I may forget. The mosque was here.

368
00:34:58,162 --> 00:35:00,096
It wasn't here.
- How can it disappear like that?

369
00:35:00,164 --> 00:35:02,132
It was on the other road.
It wasn't here. Come. Yes.

370
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:04,191
Sit. Sit.

371
00:35:21,285 --> 00:35:22,274
Let's go.

372
00:35:35,233 --> 00:35:36,222
Munira.

373
00:35:39,370 --> 00:35:43,170
Jyoti.
- I can't believe it.

374
00:35:45,243 --> 00:35:48,212
It was worse. I'm cleaning
it since yesterday.

375
00:35:49,347 --> 00:35:54,307
Do you know who has done it?
- No, I was at my aunt's.

376
00:36:04,295 --> 00:36:06,229
It's good that you were not here.

377
00:36:09,267 --> 00:36:11,326
When did this happen?

378
00:36:13,304 --> 00:36:16,239
Don't think about it
now. What's the use?

379
00:36:28,252 --> 00:36:29,219
Take this.

380
00:36:30,388 --> 00:36:31,355
I brought hiding it from mummy.

381
00:36:35,326 --> 00:36:39,285
You knew that the kitchen will be in this condition.
- No.

382
00:36:41,299 --> 00:36:42,357
I didn't think that it
would have been so burnt.

383
00:36:47,338 --> 00:36:49,363
Give it to me.
- Go, keep it outside.

384
00:37:00,284 --> 00:37:02,252
We've to go to apply
henna in the evening today.

385
00:37:02,420 --> 00:37:03,409
Are you coming?

386
00:37:05,356 --> 00:37:07,324
Have you lost it?

387
00:37:11,395 --> 00:37:19,393
Munira, look. You need money
now. They are very rich.

388
00:37:20,404 --> 00:37:23,339
Just the bride and a few more. That's it.
- No.

389
00:37:24,342 --> 00:37:26,333
5000 each for both of us.

390
00:37:28,312 --> 00:37:29,279
5.

391
00:37:31,282 --> 00:37:33,341
Truly?
- Yes, so.

392
00:37:34,318 --> 00:37:36,286
They have to pay if they
get married in such times.

393
00:37:37,355 --> 00:37:39,346
Oh, God. I'll place it outside.

394
00:37:42,460 --> 00:37:48,365
But I don't have henna. -
What? - I don't have henna.

395
00:37:48,699 --> 00:37:51,691
Don't worry. I have got lots of henna.

396
00:37:52,737 --> 00:37:53,829
You've even thought of this.

397
00:37:55,473 --> 00:37:58,465
Then? I'm your best friend, right?

398
00:38:00,344 --> 00:38:01,436
Then tell me who did all this?

399
00:38:03,414 --> 00:38:10,320
I told you I don't know. I
was at my aunt's. Leave it.

400
00:38:11,455 --> 00:38:14,390
Okay, when will we return
if we go to apply henna?

401
00:38:14,458 --> 00:38:17,393
Hanif is coming at 10.
- We are sure to come by 9.

402
00:38:20,331 --> 00:38:21,320
Oh, come.

403
00:38:21,432 --> 00:38:24,401
People have been raped, killed,
burnt alive for no fault of theirs.

404
00:38:24,502 --> 00:38:27,369
Anu, there are always
two sides to a coin.

405
00:38:27,538 --> 00:38:30,302
If those people hadn't
started this violence..

406
00:38:30,374 --> 00:38:33,400
..things wouldn't have been
this bad. No offence, Sameer.

407
00:38:34,412 --> 00:38:36,437
I can't believe you're
justifying this madness.

408
00:38:36,514 --> 00:38:38,379
Tell me. You tell me.

409
00:38:38,482 --> 00:38:41,315
When your maid eloped
with your jewellery..

410
00:38:41,419 --> 00:38:43,444
You didn't go torch the whole
Chara community, did you?

411
00:38:43,521 --> 00:38:45,421
Hey guys. Please. Come on.

412
00:38:46,490 --> 00:38:47,479
You're leaving tomorrow, right?

413
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:50,359
And can we change the topic please?

414
00:38:52,863 --> 00:38:55,923
And in any case, we too
have our own share of loss.

415
00:38:57,501 --> 00:38:59,435
A loss that's covered by insurance.

416
00:39:02,073 --> 00:39:05,167
Let's go. We've got tons to do.
- Sit.

417
00:39:06,544 --> 00:39:08,444
Hold there. That must be Rahul.

418
00:39:10,548 --> 00:39:11,537
Hail the Goddess.

419
00:39:12,483 --> 00:39:15,418
We've come to take donation
for the Goddess Lakshmi temple.

420
00:39:16,187 --> 00:39:17,176
It's okay.

421
00:39:20,191 --> 00:39:24,127
That's it. Such a big
bungalow but you are so stingy.

422
00:39:24,895 --> 00:39:26,886
Goddess Lakshmi won't be
satisfied with this much.

423
00:39:27,898 --> 00:39:29,991
My dear, whether Mother Goddess is
appeased or not, but you should be.

424
00:39:30,968 --> 00:39:31,957
You are right.

425
00:39:32,536 --> 00:39:34,470
Name?
- Sameer.

426
00:39:36,540 --> 00:39:37,507
Sameer what?

427
00:39:38,042 --> 00:39:39,031
Desai.

428
00:39:44,081 --> 00:39:46,015
Mother Lakshmi will
shower you with wealth.

429
00:39:46,584 --> 00:39:47,573
You too.

430
00:39:52,590 --> 00:39:56,390
Look, madam, you didn't turn
into a Muslim after marriage..

431
00:39:56,460 --> 00:39:59,554
..but this gentleman has turned Hindu.

432
00:40:00,464 --> 00:40:03,456
And that too with your surname.

433
00:40:04,602 --> 00:40:06,399
You don't know how many times..

434
00:40:06,470 --> 00:40:08,495
..I've silently thanked his
parents for naming him Sameer.

435
00:40:08,606 --> 00:40:10,403
Actually, I didn't even know that..

436
00:40:10,474 --> 00:40:12,567
..Sameer was a Muslim
name until I met you.

437
00:40:14,111 --> 00:40:15,442
It's in Arabic.

438
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:18,474
It means the companion who
talks to you in the evening.

439
00:40:19,250 --> 00:40:20,581
These days.. quite the whole day.

440
00:40:22,119 --> 00:40:23,586
Too scared to open his mouth.

441
00:40:31,996 --> 00:40:35,454
There were many. Everyone was shouting.

442
00:40:36,333 --> 00:40:39,359
They burnt my mother and brother too.

443
00:40:40,371 --> 00:40:44,364
They even killed my younger
sister, aunt and uncle.

444
00:40:47,344 --> 00:40:48,402
You saw all that?

445
00:40:51,382 --> 00:40:53,373
Some even brought swords.

446
00:40:58,355 --> 00:41:01,256
They killed aunt after unclothing her.

447
00:41:01,392 --> 00:41:04,361
But they didn't disrobe the men.

448
00:41:06,797 --> 00:41:08,389
And where were you?

449
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:11,458
I was hiding in the dustbin.

450
00:41:12,470 --> 00:41:13,459
Then?

451
00:41:14,071 --> 00:41:17,302
Then uncle Yusuf took
me to the survival camp.

452
00:41:17,475 --> 00:41:20,467
But I want to go to father.

453
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:24,308
Where is your father?

454
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:25,449
I don't know.

455
00:41:25,950 --> 00:41:29,283
Father had gone to the
shop when they had come.

456
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:35,459
Maybe your mother escaped.
Had she worn a black stole?

457
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:39,319
No, my mother only wears saris.

458
00:42:10,528 --> 00:42:11,517
Come here.

459
00:42:19,436 --> 00:42:20,425
Come.

460
00:42:25,476 --> 00:42:26,443
Let me see.

461
00:42:33,551 --> 00:42:36,486
My name is not Mohan, but Mohsin.

462
00:42:38,489 --> 00:42:41,549
Mohsin in the kitchen
and Mohan outside. Okay?

463
00:42:44,962 --> 00:42:47,556
I don't want to return to the camp.

464
00:42:49,833 --> 00:42:51,562
Will you stay here as Mohan?

465
00:42:52,069 --> 00:42:54,537
Will you go to look for my father first?

466
00:42:59,977 --> 00:43:01,569
They had burnt you too.

467
00:43:10,137 --> 00:43:11,172
'Brother, say something.'

468
00:43:11,172 --> 00:43:14,164
What are you telling me to
speak? What is left now to speak?

469
00:43:16,177 --> 00:43:18,008
Brother I really never knew.

470
00:43:18,078 --> 00:43:19,978
You fool, you should have checked.

471
00:43:20,114 --> 00:43:22,183
If we would have known that
the report is already filed..

472
00:43:22,183 --> 00:43:25,052
..at the police station, we wouldn't
have looked like fools there.

473
00:43:25,052 --> 00:43:26,086
But Barot had told me..

474
00:43:26,086 --> 00:43:27,110
To hell with your Barot.

475
00:43:28,155 --> 00:43:31,124
That DCP wants some scapegoat.

476
00:43:31,659 --> 00:43:34,685
He will catch two-three
like you and put behind bars.

477
00:43:34,762 --> 00:43:35,820
And the rest will go scot-free.

478
00:43:36,664 --> 00:43:40,760
Brother, I know all the names.
- Oh, my God!

479
00:43:41,202 --> 00:43:43,033
You fool, you must never be
a witness in this. Understood?

480
00:43:43,103 --> 00:43:44,127
It is a rape case. You
will be in for seven years.

481
00:43:46,173 --> 00:43:48,164
Because of you, even
I am trapped in this.

482
00:43:48,542 --> 00:43:50,009
Get some water.

483
00:43:52,179 --> 00:43:54,170
You are asking how did this happen?

484
00:43:54,882 --> 00:43:57,112
There was lot of beating.
All women are safe here.

485
00:43:57,751 --> 00:44:00,219
They are safe at the
society in the back.

486
00:44:00,621 --> 00:44:02,088
The police came at 12 at night..

487
00:44:02,523 --> 00:44:05,253
You enjoyed doing that?

488
00:44:07,528 --> 00:44:09,257
Tell me. Tell me. You
can always tell me.

489
00:44:12,233 --> 00:44:14,133
I was not the only one.

490
00:44:16,337 --> 00:44:18,703
Are you bringing water
or are you digging a well?

491
00:44:19,039 --> 00:44:21,030
I am scared.

492
00:44:21,475 --> 00:44:25,434
I'm scared.
- Don't get scared. No one comes to the kitchen.

493
00:44:25,579 --> 00:44:31,108
Sit here quietly. Sit here.
Okay? Nothing will happen.

494
00:44:31,852 --> 00:44:32,841
I promise.

495
00:44:40,261 --> 00:44:42,559
They did not think twice when
they saw these young girls.

496
00:44:44,298 --> 00:44:46,232
They dishonoured them.

497
00:44:46,367 --> 00:44:50,394
Those who don't have any honour,
how can they get dishonoured?

498
00:44:50,504 --> 00:44:51,994
And do you have any honour?

